        <ownernote>
            <para>International Truck and Engine Corporation will notify owners of this campaign on their vehicles.
                During the recall process a listing of owner names and addresses will be furnished to the involved
                dealers to enable dealers to follow up with owners and have the vehicles corrected. You must limit the
                use of this listing to this campaign because the list may contain information obtained from state motor
                vehicle registration records and the use of such motor vehicle registration data for purposes other than
                this campaign is a violation of law in several states.
            </para>
        </ownernote>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="4">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent serious eye injury, always wear safe eye protection when you perform vehicle
                        maintenance or service.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent unexpected movement of the vehicle and possible serious personal injury or death,
                        block the wheels to prevent the vehicle from moving in both directions.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <para>
                <title>DATE CODE INSPECTION</title>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the three (3) screws that fasten the lower steering column trim to the steering
                    column.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0451801" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0451801.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the underside of the turn signal stalk assembly for the build date code.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0451802" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0451802.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0451803" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0451803.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The example in Figure 3, 081304, corresponds to a build date of August 13th of 2004.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replacement of the turn signal switch is required if the build date codes are between
                    051504 (May 15, 2004) thru 062804 (June 28, 2004). Skip to step 5.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the date code on the switch assembly is NOT in the range listed in step 3, NO FURTHER
                    ACTION IS NECESSARY, re-install lower column trim panel and fasteners.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>
                <title>TURN SIGNAL SWITCH REPLACEMENT</title>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the upper column trim panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect electrical connector and remove switch assembly.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0451804" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../recallfigures/g0451804.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install new switch assembly and connect electrical connector. See Figure 4.</para>
                <para></para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">If the vehicle has a Blue Bird body, use
                        <emph type="bold">2589451C91</emph>.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">For all other vehicles and bus bodies, use
                        <emph type="bold">3587009C91</emph>.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Perform functional test on switch to verify all turn signals and hazard lamps
                    function.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install upper and lower steering column trim panels. See Figure 1.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
